minisign
------------------------------------------
Minisign is a dead simple tool to sign files and verify signatures.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.10.0-1
  libsodium23-1.0.16-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.31.0-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-5
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://jedisct1.github.io/minisign/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jedisct1/minisign/archive/0.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack minisign-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./minisign-0.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/minisign-0.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/minisign-0.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(minisign)
  /usr/bin/minisign.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/minisign.README
  /usr/share/doc/minisign/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/minisign/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/minisign.1.gz

